wiki.text:
'VIB' may refer to :
* Vlaams Instituut voor Biotechnologie (Flanders Institute for Biotechnology), a
  research center in life sciences in Flanders
* Verliebt in Berlin, a German telenovela
* Villa Constitución Airport IATA code
* Véhicule d'Intervention Blindé, a 20mm-armed version of the Véhicule de
  l'Avant Blindé used by the French Air Force.
* VMware Installation Bundle, a software package format used by VMware to
  install software on VMware ESXi

'Vib' may refer to :
* a shortening for vibration like in : ** [[Vib-Ribbon]] or [[Vib-Ripple]], two
  video games for PlayStation consoles
* Vib Gyor, a British band originating in Leeds VIB may refer to Very Important
  Bears, a line of bears put out by the North American Bear Company in the
  1980s and 90s, each of which was a bear version of an important person like
  Albert Einstein
